<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="undertake-vt">undertake <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ˌʌndə'teɪk/    美 /ˌʌndər'teɪk/  </p>
<p>(undertook, undertaken)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>承担；从事</strong></h4>
<p>to decide to do sth and start doing it：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>undertake responsibility 承担责任
</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>undertook</strong> the difficult <strong>task</strong> willingly. 
他欣然承担起了这一艰巨任务。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>接受；同意</strong></h4>
<p>to agree or promise to do sth：</p>
<ul>
<li>undertake to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He undertook to finish the job by Friday. 
他同意星期五之前完成这项工作。</p></div></div>